sp.p:
“It is awakening, because in this way one realizes emptiness, no-sign,
                            no-wish;  no-effort, no-dwelling, no coming about;
                            no object of apprehension and no-abode. Awakening is proper application.

div.p:
“In the same way, the ear is empty of a self and what belongs to a self;
                           such is its nature. This is called peace. Thoroughly understanding that the ear is empty,
                           one does not run toward sounds. Thus it is called utter peace.
